
[1]malevolence

   MALEV'OLENCE, n. [L. malevolentia; malum, evil, and volens, volo, to
   will.] Ill will, personal hatred; evil disposition towards another;
   enmity of heart; inclination to injure others. It expresses less than
   malignity.
